23
00:01:26,660 --> 00:01:28,810
I'm very sorry for my sudden absence the other day.

24
00:01:28,810 --> 00:01:32,720
No worries. Thank you for coming all the way here.

25
00:01:33,500 --> 00:01:36,120
- Please come in.
- Thank you.

26
00:01:38,750 --> 00:01:40,400
Thank you.

27
00:01:40,400 --> 00:01:41,920
Please have some coffee.

28
00:01:42,470 --> 00:01:44,240
Thank you.

29
00:01:47,090 --> 00:01:49,540
- Thank you for the coffee.
- No problem.

30
00:01:55,410 --> 00:01:57,390
It's delicious indeed.

31
00:01:57,390 --> 00:02:00,270
Is it brewed from the fair trade coffee beans?

32
00:02:00,270 --> 00:02:01,830
Yes.

33
00:02:03,160 --> 00:02:05,880
I'll now go into the final adjustments regarding the financing.

34
00:02:05,880 --> 00:02:08,060
Sure, thank you.

35
00:02:24,380 --> 00:02:26,500
The weather was good the other day,

36
00:02:26,500 --> 00:02:28,230
so we went on a picnic for the first time.

37
00:02:28,230 --> 00:02:30,230
You did? Sounds nice.

38
00:02:30,230 --> 00:02:34,540
We also brought out our tent and went to the park...

39
00:02:34,540 --> 00:02:36,720
Where do you normally go when you're outside?

40
00:02:36,720 --> 00:02:38,710
Mostly at the nearby park.

41
00:02:38,710 --> 00:02:41,510
Excuse me, you dropped this.

42
00:02:41,510 --> 00:02:44,380
- Thank you so much.
- No problem.

43
00:02:44,380 --> 00:02:46,910
You dropped it, didn't you?

44
00:02:50,540 --> 00:02:52,420
Goodbye.

45
00:03:01,390 --> 00:03:03,010
Hello?

46
00:03:03,010 --> 00:03:05,240
Sorry for the sudden call.

47
00:03:07,360 --> 00:03:11,660
Likewise, sorry for not calling you.

48
00:03:11,660 --> 00:03:13,300
<i>It's fine.</i>

49
00:03:13,300 --> 00:03:15,220
Listen.

50
00:03:16,060 --> 00:03:18,980
I hope to speak with you, Miwa-san...

51
00:03:23,890 --> 00:03:26,130
Regarding that...

52
00:03:27,720 --> 00:03:30,980
- Sorry about that.
- No worries, go ahead and answer it.

53
00:03:30,980 --> 00:03:32,930
If you'll excuse me.

54
00:03:33,720 --> 00:03:37,100
Hello, this is Fuyutsuki from Tri Ambition.

55
00:03:37,710 --> 00:03:39,450
That's right.

56
00:03:39,450 --> 00:03:42,320
We will deliver the products to you soon.

57
00:03:42,320 --> 00:03:44,200
Goodbye.

58
00:03:47,260 --> 00:03:49,270
- So sorry about that.
- It's okay.

59
00:03:49,270 --> 00:03:52,670
Mizuki normally handles the admin part of the business,

60
00:03:52,670 --> 00:03:55,730
so things are a little chaotic when she isn't around.

61
00:03:58,200 --> 00:04:01,760
It's tough when someone who's normally around isn't there, right?

62
00:04:05,090 --> 00:04:10,130
Also, regarding the difference between local and overseas sales revenue...

63
00:04:16,490 --> 00:04:19,310
- Please answer it.
- So sorry.

64
00:04:20,740 --> 00:04:23,020
Hello, Kanzaki speaking.

65
00:04:26,220 --> 00:04:29,990
No, she wasn't feverish this morning.

66
00:04:30,540 --> 00:04:32,200
Is that so?

67
00:04:33,540 --> 00:04:36,220
I'll call back later. Thanks.

68
00:04:38,460 --> 00:04:39,970
Is everything okay?

69
00:04:39,970 --> 00:04:42,210
Looks like my daughter is having a fever.

70
00:04:42,210 --> 00:04:45,140
She's with the babysitter now.

71
00:04:47,130 --> 00:04:51,900
Actually, let's continue with our discussion another day.

72
00:04:51,900 --> 00:04:53,350
No, the other day, we also didn't...

73
00:04:53,350 --> 00:04:56,250
Mizuki is also away today.

74
00:04:57,710 --> 00:04:59,620
I see.

75
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:02,150
- I shall take you up on your suggestion then.
- No problem.

76
00:05:02,150 --> 00:05:03,980
Sorry.

77
00:05:09,200 --> 00:05:12,390
Did something happen to your wife?

78
00:05:12,390 --> 00:05:14,400
No, she's fine.

79
00:05:28,330 --> 00:05:32,240
You haven't gone home in three days?

80
00:05:34,810 --> 00:05:36,900
What about Shiori-chan?

81
00:05:38,420 --> 00:05:40,450
She's with Hiroki.

82
00:05:43,010 --> 00:05:45,680
<i>Get out of this house right now.</i>

83
00:05:46,550 --> 00:05:49,870
So, Hiroki will be the one raising her?

84
00:05:52,470 --> 00:05:54,040
But Shiori-chan isn't Hiroki-san's-

85
00:05:54,040 --> 00:05:59,560
Hiroki loves Shiori... from the bottom of his heart.

86
00:06:01,420 --> 00:06:03,150
But...

87
00:06:05,870 --> 00:06:09,090
are you really okay with that, Miwa-san?

88
00:06:29,840 --> 00:06:34,650
<i>[The weather is getting colder. The thicker clothes are at the bottom-most drawer]</i>

89
00:06:42,560 --> 00:06:44,040
Sorry, Shinozaki.

90
00:06:44,040 --> 00:06:47,390
My daughter has a fever, so I have to rush home right now.

91
00:06:47,390 --> 00:06:49,350
Sorry about that.

92
00:07:21,310 --> 00:07:22,920
Kanzaki-san?

93
00:07:23,840 --> 00:07:25,360
Please get on.

94
00:07:26,120 --> 00:07:27,710
So sorry.

95
00:07:27,710 --> 00:07:29,430
No problem.

96
00:07:29,430 --> 00:07:32,660
It's on the way, since I'm headed to Toyosu.

97
00:07:33,720 --> 00:07:36,970
It's hard to get a taxi around here without an advanced booking.

98
00:07:36,970 --> 00:07:39,310
Thank you so much for your help.

99
00:07:43,650 --> 00:07:46,830
You're a really nice person, Fuyutsuki-san.

100
00:07:48,220 --> 00:07:49,960
No, I'm not.

101
00:07:51,040 --> 00:07:57,200
Such kindness hits me right in the heart now.

102
00:07:59,750 --> 00:08:01,990
What happened?

103
00:08:05,390 --> 00:08:07,140
Currently,

104
00:08:08,750 --> 00:08:11,860
I'm looking after my daughter on my own.

105
00:08:11,860 --> 00:08:15,280
And it's overwhelming, to be honest.

106
00:08:16,850 --> 00:08:20,240
I recalled something when I was drinking your coffee just now.

107
00:08:20,960 --> 00:08:25,160
It was the time when my wife was working at the flea market you organized.

108
00:08:25,770 --> 00:08:31,700
<i>Actually, I secretly went there to look for my wife.</i>

109
00:08:33,030 --> 00:08:35,660
<i>I didn't even speak to her.</i>

110
00:08:37,810 --> 00:08:40,620
I saw that she was smiling and enjoying herself.

111
00:08:41,190 --> 00:08:44,060
That caught me by surprise, and I left.

112
00:08:45,070 --> 00:08:47,940
She had never smiled like that before, not in front of me.

113
00:08:49,540 --> 00:08:51,500
I should have

114
00:08:52,260 --> 00:08:55,330
treated my wife better

115
00:08:56,440 --> 00:08:58,560
back then.

116
00:08:58,560 --> 00:09:01,940
If only I had been as kind as you, Fuyutsuki-san.

117
00:09:04,620 --> 00:09:06,560
I'm sorry for boring you with all this.

118
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:08,470
Maybe I take advantage of your kindness.

119
00:09:08,470 --> 00:09:10,070
It's fine.

120
00:09:24,540 --> 00:09:27,560
<i>[The weather is getting colder. The thicker clothes are at the bottom-most drawer]</i>

121
00:09:32,710 --> 00:09:34,620
Is everything okay?

122
00:09:37,830 --> 00:09:39,480
Your daughter, I mean.

123
00:09:41,380 --> 00:09:44,330
It's normal for children to have fevers once in a while.

124
00:09:44,330 --> 00:09:47,970
So, I don't think it'll be serious.

125
00:09:48,790 --> 00:09:50,790
Must be tough for you.

126
00:10:28,770 --> 00:10:31,900
Sir, please turn left in front.

127
00:10:33,140 --> 00:10:34,970
- So sorry to trouble you.
- No worries.

128
00:10:34,970 --> 00:10:36,820
Thank you.

129
00:11:31,970 --> 00:11:34,640
Thank you for your help today, Fuyutsuki-san.

130
00:11:34,640 --> 00:11:36,650
- No problem.
- If you'll excuse me.

131
00:11:46,240 --> 00:11:47,430
Wait, sir.

132
00:11:47,430 --> 00:11:51,410
<i>This is a problem between me and my husband.</i>

133
00:11:51,410 --> 00:11:53,920
<i>It has nothing to do with you, Fuyutsuki-kun.</i>

134
00:11:55,870 --> 00:11:57,890
Sorry.

135
00:11:57,890 --> 00:12:00,910
It's okay, please drive on.

136
00:12:16,900 --> 00:12:19,420
<i>[Children's Home - Wakaba Village]</i>

137
00:12:21,290 --> 00:12:23,410
It's snack time, everyone!

138
00:12:23,410 --> 00:12:25,990
Onee-san* has also brought juice for all of you.
<i>(T/N: A young lady or an older sister in Japanese)</i>

139
00:12:25,990 --> 00:12:27,670
<i>- Thank you, Onee-san!
- Thank you.</i>

140
00:12:27,670 --> 00:12:30,440
Put these away, put these away.

141
00:12:32,960 --> 00:12:36,200
Thank you for your donations to the orphanage.

142
00:12:36,900 --> 00:12:39,640
We look forward to supporting you moving forward.

143
00:12:39,640 --> 00:12:41,740
By the way,

144
00:12:41,740 --> 00:12:44,480
I'm sorry for my harsh words to you regarding my brother.

145
00:12:44,480 --> 00:12:46,120
No, that was because I...

146
00:12:46,120 --> 00:12:48,850
I shouldn't have said those things to the two of you.

147
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:52,550
Well...

148
00:12:53,560 --> 00:12:55,920
Please don't worry.

149
00:12:55,920 --> 00:12:58,430
I'm fine now.

150
00:13:04,520 --> 00:13:08,250
Will you be going to Africa again to set up a school?

151
00:13:08,950 --> 00:13:10,910
Yeah, we are.

152
00:13:11,480 --> 00:13:16,440
It's a dream of ours and Shimohara's, so we want to achieve that.

153
00:13:17,950 --> 00:13:20,650
Are you sure you aren't forcing yourself to do that?

154
00:13:24,590 --> 00:13:27,030
"Forget about that dream of mine."

155
00:13:27,940 --> 00:13:31,600
That's what my brother would probably have said.

156
00:13:34,250 --> 00:13:39,140
As long as the two of you keep my brother in your memories,

157
00:13:39,140 --> 00:13:41,660
it's more than enough.

158
00:13:43,320 --> 00:13:46,750
I'm happy that you see him as a dear friend,

159
00:13:47,630 --> 00:13:50,460
but I think my brother

160
00:13:50,460 --> 00:13:53,390
wouldn't want to wish that burden upon you, Mizuki-san.

161
00:13:56,140 --> 00:13:57,860
So...

162
00:13:57,860 --> 00:14:00,150
Mizuki-san...

163
00:14:00,150 --> 00:14:03,820
please cherish the life ahead of you.

164
00:14:14,470 --> 00:14:15,970
Somehow...

165
00:14:16,800 --> 00:14:20,980
it feels like Shimohara has given me a push forward from behind.

166
00:14:59,490 --> 00:15:00,850
Sorry.

167
00:15:00,850 --> 00:15:03,520
You look tired.

168
00:15:03,520 --> 00:15:08,400
The doctor has granted your mother temporary leave from the hospital.

169
00:15:10,460 --> 00:15:14,130
There's a place I haven't been to in a while. I want you to go with me.

170
00:15:14,130 --> 00:15:15,720
The two of us?

171
00:15:15,720 --> 00:15:17,440
Please.

172
00:15:21,760 --> 00:15:23,750
Thank you.

173
00:15:25,510 --> 00:15:28,940
I guess I'll stay over for the night.

174
00:15:29,650 --> 00:15:34,210
But Shiori-chan will be lonely without her mommy.

175
00:15:35,420 --> 00:15:37,120
You're right.

176
00:15:37,120 --> 00:15:39,150
I have to go home.

177
00:15:45,340 --> 00:15:47,860
Your fever has subsided. You're fine now.

178
00:15:47,860 --> 00:15:49,250
It's okay, it's okay.

179
00:15:49,250 --> 00:15:50,600
All right, all right.

180
00:15:50,600 --> 00:15:53,690
Now, now... it's okay.

181
00:15:55,250 --> 00:15:58,030
Would you like to stay in the same room as yesterday?

182
00:15:58,030 --> 00:15:59,470
Yes, sure.

183
00:15:59,470 --> 00:16:01,300
Kanzaki-sama.

184
00:16:01,300 --> 00:16:06,480
If you plan to stay for consecutive nights, I'd recommend this package here.

185
00:16:08,060 --> 00:16:10,880
Then let's do that.

186
00:16:11,860 --> 00:16:13,300
Sorry, Shinozaki.

187
00:16:13,300 --> 00:16:17,970
My daughter's fever has gone down, but I still can't hand her over to the babysitter.

188
00:16:17,970 --> 00:16:20,800
My wife also happens to be away.

189
00:16:20,800 --> 00:16:22,700
I understand.

190
00:16:22,700 --> 00:16:24,380
Please take care.

191
00:16:30,210 --> 00:16:32,600
But we need Kanzaki for today's meeting.

192
00:16:32,600 --> 00:16:34,980
We'll have to handle it somehow.

193
00:17:03,630 --> 00:17:07,060
Sorry for being away for so long.

194
00:17:09,440 --> 00:17:10,950
No worries.

195
00:17:13,250 --> 00:17:16,500
I can't handle all this on my own.

196
00:17:18,140 --> 00:17:19,660
I see.

197
00:17:37,050 --> 00:17:38,780
Fuyutsuki.

198
00:17:44,400 --> 00:17:46,080
I...

199
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,680
I wish to resign.

200
00:17:49,670 --> 00:17:52,060
What do you mean?

201
00:17:52,060 --> 00:17:54,810
I'll continue to help out until we secure Mitsukura's financing,

202
00:17:54,810 --> 00:17:58,400
and until the fair trade business gets on track.

203
00:18:01,550 --> 00:18:03,260
I'm doing this

204
00:18:04,320 --> 00:18:06,940
to bring proper closure for myself.

205
00:18:12,920 --> 00:18:17,330
The one who snatched away the person important to you

206
00:18:18,420 --> 00:18:20,010
was me.

207
00:18:22,190 --> 00:18:24,320
Back then in Africa,

208
00:18:24,320 --> 00:18:25,940
I told them that you were dead.

209
00:18:25,940 --> 00:18:27,820
The situation was chaotic, so it's understandable.

210
00:18:27,820 --> 00:18:29,630
You're wrong.

211
00:18:31,890 --> 00:18:34,930
When you said there was someone important waiting for you in Japan,

212
00:18:36,350 --> 00:18:39,740
I hated the thought of you going back to that person.

213
00:18:40,510 --> 00:18:43,270
I wanted to stop you, even if only for a while,

214
00:18:43,270 --> 00:18:45,020
so I did that on purpose.

215
00:18:49,180 --> 00:18:54,570
I didn't want you to leave me.

216
00:18:57,250 --> 00:18:59,310
At that time,

217
00:18:59,310 --> 00:19:02,180
if you had managed to inform that person waiting for you

218
00:19:02,940 --> 00:19:06,560
that you were alive,

219
00:19:08,580 --> 00:19:11,780
you'd probably be together with her right now.

220
00:19:18,340 --> 00:19:20,090
I'm so sorry.

221
00:19:21,690 --> 00:19:24,240
I've done something unforgivable.

222
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,690
You're wrong.

223
00:19:36,660 --> 00:19:40,990
It's not your fault that she and I can't be together, Risa.

224
00:19:44,770 --> 00:19:46,560
I was the one

225
00:19:47,660 --> 00:19:50,040
who did something unforgivable.

226
00:19:57,420 --> 00:20:00,010
She's someone I shouldn't have fallen in love with.

227
00:20:03,740 --> 00:20:06,950
Risa, you've done nothing wrong at all.

228
00:20:13,130 --> 00:20:16,090
This is so nostalgic.

229
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:18,410
Why did you want to come here?

230
00:20:19,740 --> 00:20:24,050
The happiest times I spent were in this town.

231
00:20:28,960 --> 00:20:31,790
Back then,

232
00:20:31,790 --> 00:20:35,460
you had a lot of fun every day.

233
00:20:37,800 --> 00:20:39,200
I did.

234
00:20:41,960 --> 00:20:46,460
I can finally see you smile.

235
00:20:47,610 --> 00:20:50,680
I'm glad we came to this place, after all.

236
00:20:53,300 --> 00:20:57,320
I've been wanting to see that smile for the last time.

237
00:20:58,850 --> 00:21:00,690
Mom...

238
00:21:03,200 --> 00:21:08,740
Thank you for always coming to my rescue.

239
00:21:11,160 --> 00:21:15,460
Remember, I'll always be on your side.

240
00:21:17,190 --> 00:21:19,860
Don't shoulder everything alone.

241
00:21:21,810 --> 00:21:25,390
Or do you think I can't be of help at all?

242
00:21:39,300 --> 00:21:45,080
I don't think I can see Shiori anymore.

243
00:21:48,620 --> 00:21:53,740
Did something happen to Shiori?

244
00:21:53,740 --> 00:21:55,890
Shiori is fine.

245
00:21:55,890 --> 00:21:58,670
But you said you can't see her anymore, right?

246
00:22:00,920 --> 00:22:02,610
Tell me.

247
00:22:11,150 --> 00:22:14,060
I'm a bad mother.

248
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:16,820
What?

249
00:22:21,020 --> 00:22:24,010
I did something unforgivable.

250
00:22:29,190 --> 00:22:31,210
Shiori...

251
00:22:36,930 --> 00:22:38,820
She...

252
00:22:42,610 --> 00:22:45,230
She isn't Hiroki's child.

253
00:22:53,010 --> 00:22:56,480
Oh, Miwa...

254
00:23:02,390 --> 00:23:06,840
And Hiroki-san... he found out?

255
00:23:13,370 --> 00:23:17,720
Why did you do something like that?

256
00:23:17,720 --> 00:23:20,840
Miwa, you...

257
00:23:23,940 --> 00:23:29,640
I've brought misery upon Hiroki and Shiori.

258
00:23:46,560 --> 00:23:48,820
I'm so sorry.

259
00:23:53,390 --> 00:23:55,620
Likewise,

260
00:23:57,180 --> 00:24:00,020
I'm a bad mother.

261
00:24:03,030 --> 00:24:07,480
I have no right to berate you.

262
00:24:58,260 --> 00:25:02,260
Is it okay if I come in?

263
00:25:06,850 --> 00:25:10,220
I'm sorry for overstepping the line.

